channel.title: Comments on: Odd things floating past the window

item.title: By: Kerr
item.dc:creator: Kerr
item.description: <p>They turned it round just outside the east entrance to Millwall docks, beside the Dome. I could see it from my desk at work. I was just leaving, when I noticed it half way round, completely blocking the river. I bet there was a few people bricking it till it was done.</p>
item.content:encoded: They turned it round just outside the east entrance to Millwall docks, beside the Dome. I could see it from my desk at work. I was just leaving, when I noticed it half way round, completely blocking the river. I bet there was a few people bricking it till it was done.

item.title: By: Matt White
item.dc:creator: Matt White
item.description: <p>@1 - I couldn't make it out sorry.<br /><br />@2 - Yes all a bit odd I know, the Thames is not wide enough for the ship to turn around, so it's been tugged up the river backwards so I assume it will leave under its own power.</p>
item.content:encoded:
@1 – I couldn’t make it out sorry.

@2 – Yes all a bit odd I know, the Thames is not wide enough for the ship to turn around, so it’s been tugged up the river backwards so I assume it will leave under its own power.
